# hotproc collection config required for deltascope process accounting
#
# 1) Enable the hotproc PMDA feature (if not already):
#    cd /var/lib/pcp/pmdas/proc && sudo ./Install
#    Answer "y" to the "hot processes" prompt during install
#
# 2) Configure the hot-process predicate in /var/lib/pcp/pmdas/proc/hotproc.conf:
#    ------------------------------------------------------
#    fname == "mysqld" || fname == "nginx" || fname == "java" ||
#    fname == "redis-server" || fname == "php-fpm" || fname == "postgres" ||
#    fname == "mongod" || fname == "dockerd" || fname == "containerd" ||
#    cpuburn > 0.01 || residentsize > 51200
#    ------------------------------------------------------
#    Meaning: the named services above are always recorded; other processes
#    join when CPU > 1% or RSS > 50MB.
#    After editing: sudo pmsignal -a pmcd; sudo pmsignal -a pmlogger
#
# 3) Have pmlogger record hotproc metrics, add to its logging config:
#    log mandatory on every 60 seconds {
#        hotproc.psinfo.utime
#        hotproc.psinfo.stime
#        hotproc.psinfo.rss
#        hotproc.psinfo.start_time
#    }
#
# 4) Verify the metrics are readable:
#    pminfo -f hotproc.psinfo.rss
